Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "upadaj" in different forms and positions:

1. *Upadaj* mi u sobu kad god želiš. (Come into my room whenever you want.)
2. Oni su *upadali* u našu teritoriju nekoliko puta prošle godine. (They invaded our territory several times last year.)
3. Nemoj *upadati* u reč drugima. (Don't interrupt others.)
4. Ona je iznenada *upala* u sobu i prekinula naš razgovor. (She suddenly burst into the room and interrupted our conversation.)
5. Ovaj ključ neće *upasti* u bravu. (This key won't fit into the lock.)
6. Sinoć je *upao* sneg, a danas je sve belo. (It snowed last night, and everything is white today.)
7. Molim te, *upoznaj* me sa svojim prijateljima. (Please introduce me to your friends.)
8. Nemoj *upadati* u dugove. (Don't get into debt.)
9. Ako ti *upadne* ideja, odmah mi javi. (If you get an idea, let me know right away.)
10. Kada *upadneš* u nevolju, uvek možeš računati na mene. (When you're in trouble, you can always count on me.)

I hope these examples help!